content:
Here's a simple example of a birthday greeting in HTML format, complete with CSS to make it more visually appealing. You can customize the name and image URL as needed:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Happy Birthday!</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .card {
            background-color: #ffebcd;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin-top: 50px;
        }
        .cake-image {
            width: 80%;
            max-width: 300px;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .message {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
        .name {
            color: #ff4500;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="card">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/300x200?text=Birthday+Cake" alt="Birthday Cake" class="cake-image">
        <div class="message">
            🎉 Happy 12th Birthday, <span class="name">Alex!</span> 🎈<br>
            We hope your day is filled with fun, laughter, and lots of cake!
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: The HTML contains a `div` with a class of `card` which holds the image and the birthday message. The name of the birthday person is highlighted using a span with the class `name`.
- **CSS Styling**:
  - The `body` has a light background color and a centered text alignment to make it visually appealing and easy to read.
  - The `.card` class styles the greeting card with a soft background color, rounded corners, and a subtle shadow for a 3D effect.
  - The `.cake-image` class ensures the image is responsive and fits well within the card.
  - The `.message` class increases the font size for readability and adds a margin for spacing.
  - The `.name` class changes the text color to orange and makes it bold to emphasize the birthday person's name.

Feel free to replace the placeholder image URL with a real image of a birthday cake and the name "Alex" with the actual name of the birthday person.
